<FIRST>r a PM-APAppointment     03-09 0105</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-AP Appointment,0109</SECOND>
<HEAD>AP Names Photo Chief In Chicago</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Robert M. Kozloff, a photographer in the Detroit
bureau of The Associated Press, has been named AP's assistant chief
of bureau for photos in Chicago.
   The appointment was announced Wednesday by Chicago Chief of
Bureau Jim Wilson.
   Kozloff is 32. He joined the AP in Detroit in 1982. He previously
worked for the Port Huron, Mich., Times Herald and for United Press
International.
   Kozloff is a native of Detroit and a graduate of Michigan State
University.
   In Chicago he succeeds Richard Horwitz, who recently became AP's
European photo network director in London.
</TEXT>
