<HEAD>Group: British Prison Inmate Population Highest In Western Europe</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: RESTORES dropped word `last' in 2nd graf.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Britain imprisons proportionately more people than
any other major West European country, an inmate aid group said
today.
   The National Association for the Care and Resettlement of
Offenders said British prisons held 55,729 people last month,
representing 98.2 prisoners for every 100,000 in the population.
   Comparative figures were Austria 96.0, Finland 93.0 and France
92.0.
   ``These disturbing figures reinforce the case for a greater use
of non-custodial penalties for non-violent offenders,'' said the
association's director, Vivien Stern.
