<DATELINE>COLUMBIA, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   John Kaplan of The Pittsburgh Press won top
honors for newspaper photographers and James Nachtwey of Magnum
Photography Services won top magazine honors in the 46th annual
Pictures of the Year competition at the University of
Missouri-Columbia School of Journalism.
   More than 1,900 photographers entered 35,000 individual
photographs for the event, said POY director Bill Kuykendall.
   The contest is co-sponsored by the National Press Photographers
Association and the School of Journalism. Awards will be presented
April 21-22 at the Missouri School of Journalism.
