<SECOND>AM-BRF--Deadly Drink,0138</SECOND>
<HEAD>Six Dead in Brazil After Drinking Industrial Alcohol</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Homemade fruit beverages made with
rubbing alcohol killed six people and left four others critically
ill in a remote Amazon town, a hospital director said Thursday.
   The victims used a new brand of rubbing alcohol to make drinks
with tropical fruit and sugar, said Leandro Vieira, director of the
Domingos Savio Hospital in Oriximina, 3,000 miles northwest of Rio.
   Four of the victims, were brought to the hospital March 1 from a
nearby village and died within 12 hours, and the other two came from
nearby villages and died a few days later, Vieira said. Four others
were hospitalized, he said.
   Oriximina, a town of 35,000 people on the Amazon River, is
accessible only by boat or plane.
