<HEAD>Carriers Have Different Policies On Accepting Tickets</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Eastern Rdp, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Continental Airlines is accepting tickets on its
sister carrier Eastern Airlines at full value, but other airlines
have different policies.
   Here is a rundown on some airline policies as of Thursday:
   _Continental: Accepts Eastern tickets.
   _TWA: Does not honor Eastern tickets.
   _Delta: Accepts full-fare Eastern tickets for confirmed seating.
Exchanges discount ticket at ticket value.
   _American: Accepts full-fare, first-class and other discount
Eastern tickets that don't carry any type of cancellation penalty.
On most Maxsaver tickets, where cancellation penalties apply,
endorsed Eastern tickets are accepted for stand-by only.
   _USAir: Accepts Eastern tickets if travelers booked portions of
their trip before Thursday on both Eastern and USAir, and USAir also
flies the Eastern segment.
   _Pan Am: Accepts Eastern tickets if an Eastern flight is a
portion of a ticket written by a different carrier.
   _Piedmont: Accepts Eastern tickets if travelers booked portions
of their trip before Thursday on both Eastern and Piedmont, and
Piedmont also flies the Eastern segment.
