<SECOND>AM-BRF--Escape Death,0178</SECOND>
<HEAD>East German News Agency Details Escape Attempt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The government news agency on Thursday detailed a
dramatic escape attempt in a hot air balloon that ended in the death
of an East German man.
   The ADN news agency said Winfried Freudenberg fell to his death
Wednesday after flying over the Berlin Wall in a homemade balloon.
   East Germany's state-run media rarely comment on escapes to West
Germany.
   The ADN report came after West Berlin police said they found the
balloon snared in a tree and Freudenberg's passport and other
belongings scattered over several hundred yards in the Zehlendorf
district of the city. Police said they also found a bank deposit
book bearing the name of his wife, Sabine.
   The news agency quoted Mrs. Freudenberg as saying she had not
accompanied her husband in the ill-fated escape attempt.
   According to official West German figures, at least 78 people
have died while trying to escape to West Berlin since East Germany
built the Berlin Wall in 1961.
