<HEAD>Pillsbury to Benefit from Cost-cutting, Marketing, Management, Chairman
Says</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pillsbury Co., acquired by Grand Metropolitan PLC
in January for $5.75 billion, will benefit from cost reductions,
marketing and management, the chairman of the British food and
liquor giant said Thursday.
   Allen Sheppard, addressing Grand Met's shareholders at their
annual meeting in London, said of Pillsbury: ``From the inside, it
looks as attractive as it did.''
   ``Pillsbury Foods is strong and well-branded, and should benefit
from cost reductions and sharp marketing.''
   Sheppard did not specify the reductions.
   The company also will benefit from ``the application of
consistent, high-quality management,'' Sheppard said. Pillsbury
``fits excellently in our worldwide strategic aims.''
   Grand Met's strategy is to focus on liquor, foods and retailing
and expand in North America and Asia, Sheppard has said repeatedly.
   In response to a question from a shareholder, Ian Martin, who is
chief executive of Grand Met's food sector and heads Pillsbury,
Sheppard said the company intends to market Pillsbury's Alpo pet
food brand in Asia, rather than in the already very competitive
European market.
   ``Our main thrust is to build up the business in Japan,'' Martin
said.
   Martin, who flew in for the meeting from Minneapolis, where
Pillsbury is headquartered, was re-elected by shareholders as a
member of Grand Met's board of directors.
   Also re-elected was George Bull, who serves as chief executive of
Grand Met's drinks sector.
   Shareholders also elected to the board included Sir Colin
Marshall, chief executive of British Airways PLC, and David Tagg,
chief executive of group services for Grand Met.
   ``With five months behind us, the year has started well and we
remain confident,'' Sheppard told shareholders.
   Grand Met's fiscal year ended Sept. 30.
   ``Grand Met is in excellent health and looks foreward to the
1990s with excitement, with health and with confidence,'' he said.
