<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Only version planned.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
235,918 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
247,038, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
in which 223,519 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 146,169 cars this week,
compared with 153,560 a week ago and 138,005 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 89,749,
compared with last week's 93,478 and last year's 85,514.
   Canadian automakers were to build 20,484 cars this week, up from
19,870 a week ago but down from last year's 21,895.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 22,347, compared
with 22,088 a week ago and 19,842 in the same week last year.
