<HEAD>London Shares Close Broadly Lower After Dull Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices closed broadly lower in dull trading
Thursday as players stepped back from the market, mostly to wait for
next Tuesday's budget speech by Chancellor of the Exchequer Nigel
Lawson.
   ``People want to see the budget out of the way,'' one dealer said.
   In the meantime, ``There's no tendency for people to want to sell
and at the same time there's no reason to want to take the market
higher either,'' he added.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index fell 7.4
points, or 0.4 percent, to 2,075.9.
   Volume was 483.9 million shares, down from Wednesday's 548.1
million shares.
