<FIRST>u f AM-OilPrices     03-09 0197</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Oil Prices,0208</SECOND>
<HEAD>Oil Prices Decline</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The energy futures market headed lower Thursday,
with wholesale home heating oil losing about a penny a gallon in
volatile trading.
   Crude oil and gasoline contracts posted more moderate declines.
   Andrew Lebow, an energy analyst with E.D.&amp;F. Man International
Futures Inc., attributed the heating-oil decline largely to
technical factors following a recent price runup.
   He said prices started out stronger, but met resistance at
certain levels and then steadily declined. That helped bring down
prices of other petroleum products, he said.
   ``I think that the underlying fundamentals seem to be bullish,
though, especially with the cold weather,'' Lebow said.
   The April contract for heating oil fell 0.99 cent to settle at
50.38 cents a gallon on the New York Mercantile Exchange, after
rising as high as 51.75 cents earlier in the session. The contract
had gained 0.29 cent Wednesday.
   April unleaded gasoline, which rose 0.44 cent Wednesday, settled
down 0.25 cent to 51.60 cents.
   The April contract for West Texas Intermediate, the benchmark
grade of U.S. crude oil, closed at $18.52 a barrel, down 2 cents.
The contract had risen 24 cents in the previous session.
</TEXT>
